<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Signs of Frenchmen to Flood to Diana Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 4 (Xinhua) -- There is no sign that Frenchmen
and Frenchwomen will flood to attend the funeral of the late
Princess of Wales Diana Spencer at Westminster Abbey in London on
Saturday, said French railway, air and travel companies today.
</P>
<P>
The French state railway company SNCF told Agence France-Presse
(AFP) that the situation is "calm" and no supplementary Eurostar
train is planned for London this weekend.
</P>
<P>
Air France said that no special schedule is made, as the planes
for London are always fully ordered for the weekend as usual.
</P>
<P>
The Degriftour travel agency said that the number of tourists
for London is expected to increase between 12 percent and 15
percent, while the Public Tours agency, which is specialized in
trips to Britain, only expects a slight increase of tourists this
weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Nouvelle Frontieres air company said there is no increase
of orders from passengers to London, and the Havas Voyages which
is linked with the air company reported some cancellations because
some people cannot "stand the crowd".
</P>
<P>
France will be officially represented by its ambassador to
Britain, Jean Gueguinou, at the funeral of Diana.
</P>
<P>
The French first lady, Bernadette Chirac, former President
Giscard d'Estaing and his wife, Anne-Aymone, will attend the
funeral in private, according to AFP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
