<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Purchase Russian Jet Fighters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia has agreed to
purchase 12 Sukhoi 30k jet fighters and eight MI-17-IV helicopters
from Russia for a total of 500 million U.S. dollars, a senior
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Under a counter-purchase agreement, Russia has agreed to buy
from Indonesia 40 kinds of commodities which are also worth 500
million U.S. dollars, State Minister for Development Planning
Ginandjar Kartasasmita said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said a memorandum of understanding on the purchase
of the Russian aircraft was signed on August 29 while the
purchasing contract will be signed on October 29.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement reached during Ginandjar's recent
visit to Moscow, Russia will buy from Indonesia various products,
such as natural rubber, cement, fertilizer, textile and textile
products, footwear, plywoods, toys, cigarettes and chemical
products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
