<HEADLINE> Albright Middle East Under Reconsideration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A scheduled trip by
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright to the Middle East would be
reconsidered following the bomb attack in a Jerusalem mall today,
the State Department said.
</P>
<P>
The trip "is under evaluation" as Albright, at present on
vacation in Europe, had made security a precondition for
travelling to the area.
</P>
<P>
Three bombs went off at around 3:00 p.m. local time within 15
minutes of each other in a big mall in Jewish western Jerusalem,
killing at least six and injuring more than 150.
</P>
<P>
Albright planned to meet Syrian President Hafez al-Assad and
Palestinian leader Arafat during the trip designed to revive the
stalled Middle East peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
