<HEADLINE> Mubarak Condemns Suicide Jerusalem Explosions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
condemned the suicide bomb explosions in central Jerusalem a few
hours ago which killed at least six people and injured 165 others.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the press today, Mubarak called upon the
concerned parties to exercise self restraint during these
difficult circumstances.
</P>
<P>
The terror blasts, aimed at innocent civilians, only led to
further complication of the critical situation and posed
obstruction to the peace process in the region, Mubarak said.
</P>
<P>
"I reiterate that the best method to address acts of terrorism
and bloodshed is to proceed forward with the peace process, and
that all parties adhere to their signed agreements," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak affirmed that resorting to collective punishment
against Palestinians would further fuel tension and complicate the
situation.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the explosion, Israel reimposed the total
closure of the Palestinian self-rule territories of West Bank and
Gaza Strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
