<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Embargo on S. Leone Illegal, Junta Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone's military junta
today made its first official response to the economic embargo
enforced by west African countries, saying that the move lacked
legal basis.
</P>
<P>
The sub-regional leaders decided at a summit last week to
impose economic sanctions and embargo on Sierra Leone as a means
to force the junta to give up power it seized in the May 25 coup.
</P>
<P>
But a spokesman of the junta denied the resolution, saying
that the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) had
no responsibility to do so.
</P>
<P>
"The only body that is responsible to establish sanctions is
the United Nations Security Council. What the ECOWAS has to do is
to make recommendations," the spokesman said, quoted by the
British Broadcasting Corporation.
</P>
<P>
"The UN has not met. Nothing has been established. And it is
the responsibility of the government, which is a responsible
government, to take care of life and property," he said.
</P>
<P>
The coup in Sierra Leone has invited unanimous condemnation of
the international community. ECOWAS has sent troops there in an
attempt to restore the legitimate government ousted in the coup.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations between ECOWAS and the junta broke down at the
end of July when the junta announced to remain in power until the
year 2001.
</P>
<P>
ECOWAS heads of state met at a summit last weekend in Abuja,
Nigeria and decided to enforce economic sanctions and embargo on
the troubled country in a bid to force the junta to step down.
</P>
<P>
While the junta is reportedly looking for ways to re-open
talks with ECOWAS, the Nigerian military warned Wednesday that
the coupists were planning to launch offensive attack on troops
sent to Sierra Leone by ECOWAS.
</P>
<P>
The junta also accused the sub-regional troops of shelling
civilian targets in Freetown in the past 40 hours, killing 50
civilians with 17 seriously wounded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
