<HEADLINE> Tanzania's Capital City needs Improvement of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Unplanned development
in Dar es Salaam is one of the major factors that incapacitate
the City Commission from keeping the environment clean.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made here today by Richard Msingi, City
Commission Sustainable Coordinator, at a three-day consultive
meeting on the City Health Plan.
</P>
<P>
Msingi said that influx of people from other regions has
caused an increase of population to an extent that the city fails
to provide baisc environmental services.
</P>
<P>
The population of Dar es Salaam is 2.3 million now, compared
to 1.4 milion in 1988. The population growth rate is about 7
percent per annum.
</P>
<P>
The City Commission has taken measures to improve the social
sector, which include emergence-clean up campaigns, improvement
of the work of hospitals, health centers and dispensaries through
the Urban Health Project program and anti-malaria control
program.
</P>
<P>
However, Msingi said, social services in the city are still in
pathetic situation as the population growth rate is not
proportional to the available socio-economic services since the
city's economic growth rate is lower.
</P>
<P>
Msingi cited another factor as underfinancing. He appealed to
interested donors for supplement its efforts to improve the
city's environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
