<HEADLINE> Sit-in in Beirut for Detainees In Israeli Jails </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese National Committee of
Detainees in Israeli Jails today staged a sit-in in front of the
Beirut office of the International Red Cross Committee (IRCC) in a
sign of support for Lebanese detainees in Israeli prisons.
</P>
<P>
The Labenese National News Agency quoted the president of the
committee Mohammed Oubeid as saying that the release of Lebanese
detainees in Israeli prisons has become a part of the struggle
with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The current task for the committee is to call on the
international community such as IRCC to further press Israel to
improve the detainees' conditions in prisons, and allow all
international human rights organizations to visit prisons and
witness what is goning on, he added.
</P>
<P>
meanwhile, he called on Israel to immediately release the
diseased, women and children from its jails and allow a medical
team to enter and check health of the others.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the committee said the Lebanese
detainees in Israeli prisons are suffering from various mental
and physical tortures, including electrical hit, continuous hit by
electrical wire, hanging on the pillar under the burning sun in
summer and in the rain.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel established a 1,100-square-kilometer "security
zone" in south Lebanon in 1985 to buffer attacks by Islamic
militants on northern Israel, it has set up several prisons to
detain those who refuse obedience to Israel or cooperate with them.
</P>
<P>
The Khiam Detention Camp, the biggest one, now reportedly holds
about 140 Lebanese detainees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
