<HEADLINE> Britain Condemns Jerusalem Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The British government has
strongly condemned suicide bombings in Jerusalem early today,
saying "the terrorists must be brought to justice."
</P>
<P>
Israeli police sources said eight people, including three
suicide bombers, have been killed and about 150 wounded in the
attacks at the main Ben-Yehuda shopping center.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued this afternoon, British Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook said: "I utterly condemn this horrific series of bombs
in the heart of West Jerusalem."
</P>
<P>
"The cold-blooded murder of innocent civilians in a crowded
shopping center is beneath contempt. The terrorists must be
brought to justice," Cook said.
</P>
<P>
He made it clear that this atrocity "makes it all the more
important for the Israelis and Palestinians to return to full
dialogue and to cooperate in the fight against terrorism so that
peace is restored on the streets." 
</P>
