<HEADLINE>  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 4 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
today condemned a bombing attack in Jerusalem early today.
</P>
<P>
In a message addressed to Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu and issued by the Elysee presidential office, Chirac
expressed his ``sadness and solidarity'' with Israel and hoped
that the Middle East peace process should not be ``the victim of
terrorism.''
</P>
