kabila took power of DRC in May after his armed force,
Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire
overwhelmed the then government troops led by Mobutu Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela has said that South
Africa will set up a team under Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo to
look into the allegations, noting his government does not want
the country to be a base for destablizing any country. 
