chairman of a parliamentary party cannot act as a chairman of the
Duma at the same time.
</P>
<P>
Shokhin, 46, was once Minister of Economy and Vice-Prime
Minister before becoming the first vice-chairman of the state Duma
in January 1996. He was elected chairman of the "Our House-Russia"
party in parliament Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The appointment of Shokhin to head the parliamentary "Our
House-Russia" party was aimed at improving its political status in
the parliament, and its political life in the country.
</P>
<P>
A new first vice-chairman of the state Duma will be elected
later, again from representatives of the "Our House-Russia"
movement in the parliament, the report said.  
