<HEADLINE> Chinese And Saint Lucia Foreign Ministers Confer in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen, in talks today with George Odlum, Minister
of Foreign Affairs and International Trade of Saint Lucia, said
that China is ready to develop its relations with the eastern
Carribean nations on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful
Co-existence.
</P>
<P>
Odlum, whose visit comes shortly after the establishment of
diplomatic relations between the two countries, said that this
shows the great importance attached by the government of Saint
Lucia to bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Qian said he believes that Odlum's visit will help lay a sound
foundation for overall development of friendly and co-operative
ties, and even though the two countries are far apart, the Chinese
people have always cherished friendly feelings for the people of
Saint Lucia.
</P>
<P>
When Saint Lucia declared independence, he said, China's
premier sent congratulations and the Chinese government sent
representatives to attend the celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the Chinese government has been active in
developing friendly and co-operative relations with Saint Lucia,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the two countries have their respective
characteristics and that they face the same task of vitalizing
their own economies and improving people's standard of living, but
that he believes there are bright prospects for relations.
</P>
<P>
Odlum said that he was pleased to visit China when the two
countries established diplomatic relations, which widened the area
of bilateral co-operation and created favorable conditions for
further development of relations between China and other eastern
Carribean nations.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China attaches great importance to its economic
and trade co-operation with Saint Lucia and that close
co-operation between the governments of the two countries is very
important.
</P>
<P>
Odlum said that because China is the biggest developing country
in the world and a friend of developing nations, there is a solid
foundation for co-operation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that Saint Lucia agrees with China's proposal that the
two governments increase co-operation, and encourage entrepreneurs
to have more exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China attaches great importance to relations
with Latin American and Carribean nations, and that China
officially joined the Carribean Development Bank not long ago and
established an official dialog with the South America Common
Market. China also filed applications for observers for the Latin
American Parliament and the Association of Carribean States, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Odlum said that Saint Lucia highly values its sovereignty and
sticks to internationally-recognized norms, and that his nation
will follow the "one China" policy and will never have official
ties with Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
