<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Japanese Prime Minister-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting today with Ryutaro Hashimoto, who is making his first
official visit to China as prime minister, said that China and
Japan should advance their bilateral friendship for generations to
come.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should strictly observe the Sino-Japanese
Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace and
Friendship when promoting bilateral relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders had an important meeting in Manila last
November that played a significant and positive role in improving
and developing bilateral relations, Jiang noted, adding that he
hoped Hashimoto's visit, which comes on the 25th anniversary of
normalization of diplomatic relations between the two countries,
will help advance bilateral ties in a healthy and steady way.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto said he was honored to meet with Jiang again, and
that maintaining constant contacts between leaders of the two
countries is important for bilateral relations and that he hopes
his visit will serve as a new starting point in Japan-China
relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that China-Japan relations are entering a
significant period, inheriting the past and ushering in the
future, and that this relationship will have a heavy impact on
both countries, the region and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
When Chairman Mao and Premier Zhou Enlai were alive, they said
that the two peoples should be friendly to each other for
generations, and with the new century drawing near, this goal
remains, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"We hold that both sides should continue to strictly abide by
the principles set in the joint statement and the peace and
friendship treaty, and properly handle the existing problems
between the two countries in the spirit of seeking common grounds
while reserving differences, as this is the important guarantee to
realize the goal," Jiang stressed.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Jiang went on to say, leaders of both
countries should understand and handle, with a long-term and
strategic perspective, the bilateral relationship and usher in a
healthy and steady Sino-Japanese relationship into the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto stated that due to efforts of the older political
figures in the two countries, Japan and China normalized their
diplomatic ties in 1972 and that in the past 25 years, the
promotion of bilateral ties are based on the joint statement and
the peace and friendship treaty.
</P>
<P>
The principles set in these two political documents will remain
the guidelines for the relations between the two countries, the
prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
He stated that Japan is ready to advance a long-term friendly
relationship with China in accordance with the two documents.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that in reviewing the contact history of the two
nations, friendship is the mainstream in the past 2,000 years or
more.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, in modern times, Japanese militarists waged
wars of aggression against China, causing great losses and
suffering to the Chinese, and the Japanese people were made to
suffer a lot themselves. Correctly understanding and viewing this
period of history is of great importance for the future of the two
nations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
