<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Industrial Sales Up in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Industrial sales in the
Philippines reached 204.6 billion pesos (around 6.8 billion U.S.
dollars) in the first half of the year, an increase of 11 percent
over the same period last year, the Philippine News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
A survey conducted by the Department of Trade and Industry
shows that 12 of the country's 21 sectors posted positive growth
during the period.
</P>
<P>
The garments sector is the highest earner, rebounding from last
year's lackluster performance to a revenue of 36.6 billion pesos
(1.2 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The survey attributes the growth to the greater demand for
Philippine apparel products from the United States, Japan and
European countries.
</P>
<P>
Electronics, the second biggest earner, shows the highest
growth rate of 33 percent. It is followed by the food processing
industry.
</P>
<P>
The biggest loser is still the sugar sector, of which the sales
plummeted further by 58 percent due to the stiff competition with
the cheaper imported sugar in the domestic market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
