<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Calls on Palestinians to Stop ``Gears of Terror'' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 5 (Xinhuua) -- France today called on
Palestinians to ``do all they can to stop the gears of terror.''
</P>
<P>
The call issued after a triple suicide bombing by suspected
Palestinian terrorists killed seven people and wounded 170 in
Jerusalem on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
``The peace process is threatened even in its foundation. All
should be done by the Palestinian side to put an end to the gears of
terror, all should be done by the Palestinian side to save the
achievements of the concluded accords,'' said French Foreign
Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that France is deeply worried by the latest
attack in Jerusalam and calls on Israel and Palestinians to ``revive
the logic of peace.''
</P>
<P>
``Only a negotiated, just and lasting peace could procure to all
the peoples of the region the security to which they aspire,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
French President Jacques Chirac today made telephone calls to
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu and Lebanese Prime Minister Rafic Hariri, urging them to
``give back a little hope to the peace process.''
</P>
<P>
Chirac expressed his hope that the peace process could be
relaunched with the forthcoming visit by the United States Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright to the Middle East, said French
presidential office.
</P>
<P>
``The president of the republic is following very closely the
dramatic evolution of the situation in the Middle East,'' said
French officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
