<HEADLINE> HK to Host Etchells World Yachting Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Preparations for the OOCL
Etchells World Yachting Championship are well underway, organizers
said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The championship, slated for November 5 to 17 here, is the
fourth and last regatta of the OOCL World Series. Before the
world championship there will be the OOCL Hong Kong China
Championship for November 1-5, this year, which is the third leg
in the series.
</P>
<P>
The two regattas are to be held in the waters south of Lamma
Channel of Hong Kong Island.
</P>
<P>
Skippers who collect the highest accumulated points over the
three-year, four-regatta series, will win the OOCL World Series
Trophy.
</P>
<P>
This year's races are expected to attract the largest number of
and most competitive sailors. Among them are John Bertrand of
America's Cup fame and past Asia Pacific Champions and world
number two Jud Smith, and Poul Ricard Hoj-Jensen, a former Olympic
champion, according to the organizers.
</P>
<P>
Now leading the points standings are Warwick Downes and Mark
Thornburrow from Hong Kong, China, largely due to their consistent
top finishes in the first two regattas -- the OOCL fourth and OOCL
fifth championships in November, 1995 and 1996 respectively.
</P>
<P>
This year's championships will draw sailors from different
countries and regions including Australia, New Zealand, the United
States, Britain, Italy, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) and, for the first time, China.
</P>
<P>
It is also the first time that an international sailing event
will take place in the Hong Kong SAR, which was established on
July 1 this year, after Hong Kong's handover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
