<HEADLINE> Tung Says First Overseas Trip "Very Useful" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, Chief
Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
described his first overseas trip as "very useful, constructive
and successful," a Hong Kong SAR Government spokesman told
reporters here today.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive believed that leaders in Singapore and
Malaysia could see that Hong Kong was running smoothly and that
Hong Kong's lifestyle remained unchanged, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Tung was quoted as saying that they were all very happy about
the return of Hong Kong to China, the smoothly functioning of the
SAR Government for the last two months and the implementation of
the concept of the "One Country, Two Systems".
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Tung held a private meeting late this
afternoon with Singapore's Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew, of whom,
the chief executive said "he is a great statesman whom I respect a
great deal."
</P>
<P>
"We had some very useful discussion. He's obviously happy to
see the transition has been smooth and things going on well in
Hong Kong," Tung was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We also talked about the currency turmoil recently and about
the stock market turmoil. It was a very useful and very helpful
discussion," he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this afternoon, the chief executive met with
Singaporean Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for Defense Dr.
Tony Tan and discussed with him the expanding application of
information technology in schools and communities.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that housing supply and renovation, the
qualities of housing, tenant facilities and housing design were
among the topics discussed during the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tung will return to Hong Kong on Saturday morning and leave
for a five-day visit to the United States on Monday morning, the
spokesman said.  
</P>
