<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Condemns Bombing in Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today condemned the suicide bombing in downtown West Jerusalem
Thursday, and called for a "resolute and uncompromising fight"
against such terrorist acts.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process would not be hampered by
terrorists and extremist force and it would withstand any attack
from the anti-peace camp, Yeltsin was quoted by his press
secretary Sergei Yastrzhembsky as saying.
</P>
<P>
Three suicide bombers and four other people were killed in the
attack in a pedestrian mall packed with people. At least 165
others were injured in the bombing, which came just five weeks
after another suicide attack killed 17 in the same neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Foreign Ministry also joined in criticism today
against the terrorists and urged Israelis and Palestinians to
return to the negotiation table.
</P>
<P>
It said in a statement that by the bombing, the extremists were
trying to provoke the Israelis and to block a healthy development
of the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the best response to such act would be
Palestinians and Israelis resuming peace talks, which have been
stalled since March when Israel broke ground to build a
controversial Jewish settlement in Arab east Jerusalem. 
