<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Japanese Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, met with
visiting Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto in the Great
Hall of the People this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that bilateral relationship has undergone extensive
development and expanded in depth under the new historical
conditions since the normalization of Sino-Japanese relations 25
years ago. He also noted that cooperation between China's National
People's Congress and the Japanese Diet has expanded greatly.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan are both influential countries in the region
and throughout the world. The development of good neighborly
relations and the advancement of mutually beneficial
cooperation conform to the fundamental interests of both
countries and to the peace, development and stability of the
region and the world as a whole, said Qiao.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that both sides should summarize the experience and
lessons in the development of bilateral relations over the past 25
years. Both sides should uphold the principles and spirit of the
Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace
and Friendship, and should use said documents as the political
basis for jointly advancing the steady and health development of
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also pointed out the existence of two major issues in
the bilateral relations following the normalization of their
relations -- the issue of history and the issue of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the Japanese government should adopt a
responsible attitude towards history, treat relevant issues in a
conscientious manner, and continue to follow the road of peace and
development.
</P>
<P>
Qiao addressed the Taiwan issue by noting that Japan should
earnestly value and respect China's stand and adhere to the
principles defined in the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the
Sino-Japanese Treaty of Pace and Friendship.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto said that Japan and China have increased exchanges
and cooperation on international issues since the the
normalization of bilateral relations, in addition to frequently
arranging exchanges between the NPC and the Diet.
</P>
<P>
He promised that Japan would continue to abide by the
principles of the Joint Statement and the Treaty of Peace and
Friendship, follow the road of peace and development, maintain
friendly ties with China and refrain from interfering in China's
internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Liu Zhongli, who also serves as chairman of
the Chinese government reception committee, and Vice-Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan also attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
