<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Suspect Arrested in Stockhoom anti-Olympics bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A suspect in two powerful
bombings in Sweden was arrested late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Last month, bombs destroyed huge parts of the Olympic stadium
in Stockholm and the Ullevi stadium in Goeteborg.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old men was caught when he tried to blow up the
statue used as the symbol for the Stockholm's candidacy.
</P>
<P>
Chief of Stockholm's bid for the site of the 2004 Summer
Olympics said that the action showed Sweden would not let "the
voice of violence silence the voice of the sport."
</P>
<P>
The suspect's name was not immediately released, according to
judicial custom.
</P>
<P>
The bombings had casted a shadow over Stockholm's chances for
staging the Olympics, though no one was injured in the powerful
blasts.
</P>
<P>
The arrest came hours before the International Olympic
Committee was to choose among Stockholm and four other candidates
for the 2004 Games, during a meeting in Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
</TEXT>
