<HEADLINE> Anderlecht Admit Giving Money to Referee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Belgian soccer club
Anderlecht on Friday admitted that they had paid one million
francs (27,000 U.S. dollars) to the referee of their 1984 UEFA Cup
semifinal against England's Nottingham Forest.
</P>
<P>
Club chairman Roger Vanden Stock confirmed newspaper statements
by his father Constant, the former chairman, that the money was
paid to Spanish referee Guruceta Muro on April 26 1984 -- the day
after the second leg of the semifinal which Anderlecht won 3-0.
</P>
<P>
That gave them a 3-2 aggregate victory and took them into the
final which they eventually lost on penalties to Tottenham Hotspur
of England. 
</P>
</TEXT>
