<HEADLINE> 12 Israeli Soldiers Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 Israeli soldiers
were killed this morning in fighting with Lebanese troops and
guerrillas in south Lebanon, security sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
This has partly been confirmed by news from Israel, which in an
army statement said 11 soldiers died and one was missing in the
battle, now presumed dead.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued by the Lebanese army said that an Israeli
airborne commando launched a pre-dawn raid on the village of
Insariyeh, about 45 kilometers north of the Israeli border.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli forces were immediately spotted by the Lebanese
troops and guerrillas of the Shiite Muslim militant Amal movement
and Hezbullah stationed in the area, who promptly opened fire, the
communique said.
</P>
<P>
The fighting lasted more than two hours and the Israelis
suffered some 20 casualties. Four of the wounded were rescued by
Israeli gunships.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that during the battle, a Lebanese army
position was hit, leaving a woman and a baby girl dead, a Lebanese
soldier and six civilians wounded.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese security sources said four Amal guerrillas and two
Hezbullah fighters were also injured in the clashes.
</P>
<P>
The pre-dawn raid, hours after a triple suicide bombing tore
through the heart of Jerusalem's western sector, was meant to
retaliate an Amal attack last week in which five Israeli soldiers
were killed.
</P>
<P>
But local reports said today's fighting dealt the worst
casualties for Israeli forces in a single battle in the area in
more than 12 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
