<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Remains Bullish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The upward trend in trading
on the Shanghai Stock Exchange (SSE) continued this week despite a
slight drop in the trading volume
</P>
<P>
The SSE Comprehensive Index closed the week at 1,251.55 points,
up 2.5 percent over last week, with the SSE 30 Index rising by
1.32 percent to end at 3,809.7 points.
</P>
<P>
The week's trading volume totaled 26.21 billion yuan, down 1.94
percent from last week.
</P>
<P>
Blue chip stocks such as Yizheng Chemical Fiber, Shanghai
Petrochemical and Ma'anshan Iron and Steel remained as the market
leaders this week, while investors gradually turned from lower
priceed shares to medium- and high-priced issues.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts attribute the continued upward momentum on the
bourse to the public's growing confidence in the state-owned
enterprises, which are expected to enter a new phase of reform
following the 15th Congress of the Communist Party of China due to
open September 12.
</P>
<P>
The latest issue of state bonds valued at 13 billion yuan was
completed this week and had only limited effect on the market, and the
fact that most bonds were purchased by banks and stock dealers had
little effect on the market's money supply.
</P>
<P>
Middle-year reports for listed firms have been published and
investors are gradually gained increasing confidence. Local
experts predict a new round of upward trading on the
market. 
</P>
