It will be followed by the 1997 Eco-World Congress, Africa's
first conference on investment opportunities in wildlife and
nature-based tourism, which will take place in Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
The World Tourism Organization will also hold a seminar on
tourism taxation at the end of the exhibition in South Africa on
September 20.
</P>
<P>
South Africa topped the tourism revenue for Africa last year
with 1.74 billion U.S. Dollars while Kenya the second with 493
million Dollars. 
