<HEADLINE> Turkey to Buy Five Minesweepers from France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Navy has decided to
purchase five Cirse class minesweepers from France to boost its
defense capacity.
</P>
<P>
Local English newspaper Daily News today quoted senior
military sources, who declined to be named, as saying that the
50-million-U.S.-dollar deal was signed under the French surplus
arms program.
</P>
<P>
The five vessels are expected to arrive in Turkish seaports in
the coming months, sources said without specifying.
</P>
<P>
At present, Turkey has a fleet of more than 30 aged
minesweepers, mostly U.S.-made, which need to be upgraded.
</P>
<P>
France, one of the major arms exporters in the world, has been
intensifying its contacts with the Turkish military over the past
months when Turkey suffered an arms embargo from Washington.
</P>
