<HEADLINE> China Striving to Strengthen Trade Ties with Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- China will promote cooperation
with African countries in all fields and expand trade and economic
links between the two sides, according to Vice-Premier Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to a national workshop on economic and trade
cooperation with Africa which ended today in Dalian, Li said
Africa has abundant resources, a vast market and great potential
for development. Over the past few decades, China has attached
importance to expanding economic and trade links with African
countries. China has provided gratis aid free of any political
conditions to promote economic growth in Africa. African countries
have expressed sincere gratitude for the invaluable help provided
by China.
</P>
<P>
The three-day workshop, the first of its kind held in China,
focused on studying arrangements for strengthening economic and
trade cooperation with Africa.
</P>
<P>
Li said China will place additional impetus on economic and
trade cooperation with Africa and will extend the scope of
cooperation, and that China will pursue a strategy of developing
economic and trade links through all channels, providing high
quality goods and services, and building diversified markets.
</P>
<P>
China will accelerate reforming its overseas aid program, and
will promote all forms of cooperation between enterprises of the
two sides in order to put a new face on economic and trade
cooperation between China and Africa, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed to the fact that China is the largest developing
country, while Africa is the largest developing continent. He said
the common historical mission, development goals and interests of
the two sides have promoted cooperation between China and Africa
on the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
He said that cooperation is not only of great strategic
significance for economic growth of Asia and Africa in the next
century, but also for "South-South" cooperation and the overall
peace and stability of the world. He added that cooperation will
expand the dimensions of China's opening drive and will inject
new vigor into the country's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the symposium conducted highly-beneficial
exploration into how to strengthen all-round cooperation with
Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
