<HEADLINE> National Troupe To Stage Two Classic Ballets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The National Ballet Troupe of
China (NBTC) will stage two classics ballets -- "Sleeping Beauty"
and "Swan Lake" -- between September 27 - October 7 in Beijing as
part of the '97 China International Opera and Ballet Year.
</P>
<P>
The NBTC staged a number of ballet classics earlier this year,
including "Don Quixote", "the Nutcracker" and "Giselle". The
troupe also staged the modern Chinese ballet "The Red Detachment
of Women" last month to the delight of the local audience.
</P>
<P>
The China Performing Arts Agency (CPAA), the organizer,
announced that the NBTC has invited Monica Parker and William
Tuckett, two famous artists with the British Royal Ballet Troupe,
to assist Chinese dancers during the rehearsals of "Sleeping
Beauty".
</P>
<P>
Yuan Ping, an official with CPAA, said the agency has organized
numerous cultural exchanges between the NBTC and leading ballet
troupes from Russia, Sweden, France, Britain, and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Chinese artists have exerted great efforts to improve ballet
performances in recent years, Yuan said, adding that the CPAA has
developed a large market for excellent NBTC performances which
have enabled Chinese audience to learn more about the art form.
</P>
<P>
NBTC Director Zhao Ruheng noted that a number of Chinese
dancers have won gold medals in international competitions over
the past five years. "Their performances represent the country's
highest standard of ballet," according to this Chinese ballerina
who has performed with a number of famous foreign ballet dancers
and troupes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
