<HEADLINE> 4 Rebels Killed in Clashes With Troops in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 5 (Xinhua) -- At least four Tamil rebels
were killed and three others injured Thursday night in renewed
fighting with government troops in Northern Province of Sri Lanka,
military sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) fired mortars on the troops strengthening defenses
southwest of Nedunkerni.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated with mortar and artillery fire, killing
at least four rebels and wounding three others.
</P>
<P>
One soldier was injured in the fighting, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The troops continue to dominate areas around Puliyankulam Town.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting with government troops since 1983
for a separate state in the north and east of the island country.
 
