<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cities Encouraged To Clean Themselves While Developing Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- China conferred the title of
"Model City in Environmental Protection" today on the five coastal
cities of Xiamen, Dalian, Zhuhai, Shenzhen and Weihai.
</P>
<P>
The title is the country's highest honor in the field. The
cities which receive the recognition must have an overall clean
environment while witnessing rapid social and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
East China's Zhangjiagang earned the honor last year.
</P>
<P>
Xie Zhenhua, director of the National Environmental Protection
Agency (Nepa) said during a press conference here today that the
selection of model cities in environmental protection will further
push forward the country's urban pollution control, and the
improvement of urban environment and people's quality of life.
</P>
<P>
He added that it has great significance for carrying out the
strategy of sustainable development in urban areas and for
bringing the country closer to the world.
</P>
<P>
Ever since China decided to choose model cities in
environmental protection this June, many cities have responded
enthusiastically.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that candidates are assessed in terms of economy,
environment quality, environmental protection and management. More
than 20 indices, including economic growth rate, air pollution
index, sewage treatment rate and natural reserve coverage rate,
were used in the judging.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said that the five cities, although different in
size, industrial structure and course of development, have
witnessed steady and healthy growth over the years. Their social
and economic growth level and environmental quality all take the
lead in the country.
</P>
<P>
Nepa said that it will regularly check the six cities that have
received recognition, and recall the title of any who fall short
of the requirements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
