<HEADLINE> Stadium Collapse Kills 32 in Paraguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A portion of a sports
stadium in eastern Paraguay collapsed during a political
convention, killing at least 32 people, media reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the Paraguayan capital, Asuncion, said that at
least 100 others were injured, some seriously, when a metallic
section of the stadium caved in Thursday night in the border town
of Ciudad del Este, 290 kilometers east of Asuncion.
</P>
<P>
Local members of the ruling Colorado Party were at the stadium
to choose candidates to run in departmental elections, set for
Sunday, according to the Asuncion newspaper Noticias.
</P>
<P>
Some believe that the tragedy was caused by powerful winds,
possibly a tornado, that damaged the structure Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The dead included four police officers and three children, said
Juan Carlos Barreto, mayor of Ciudad del Este, radio reports
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
