<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Special Article: Great Banner (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading national newspaper, opened another special column of
special articles to greet forthcoming 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), the congress. This is the
first in a series of articles entitled the "Great Banner."
</P>
<P>
In an editor's note, the paper noted that the whole party and
the people throughout the country have scored gratifying
achievements over the past 20 years, especially since the 14th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) was held
in 1992 under the leadership of the Party Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Excerpts of the People's Daily special article "Great
Banner" follow:
</P>
<P>
The CPC 15th National Congress will be convened in a crucial
historical period when the country's reform, opening-up and
socialist modernization drives have inherited the past and are
ushering in the future.
</P>
<P>
The entire world will undoubtedly focus on what banner the
congress will uphold and what road it will follow.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin incisively pointed out in a May 29 speech delivered
at the Party School of the CPC Central Committee that "the banner
refers to the direction in which China will proceed and the image
it will present." Jiang demanded that all Party members, senior
leaders in particular, maintain a high degree of consciousness and
adamancy regarding the issue of banner.
</P>
<P>
The CPC has adhered to Marxism-Leninism guidelines ever since
its founding. "Seventy-six years of arduous revolutionary and
construction causes have enabled the CPC to achieve two
theoretical leaps through a combination of the basic principles of
Marxism-Leninism and specific conditions in China," according to
Hou Shudong, vice-president of the University of National Defense.
</P>
<P>
"In the wake of the first leap, the Party, led by late Chairman
Mao Zedong, produced Mao Zedong Thought, a revolutionary theory
concerning the building of a new China, with the second leap
witnessing the birth of the theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics set forth by the Party with Deng Xiaoping
as its chief representative."
</P>
<P>
Over the past 20 years, China has advanced forward under the
guidance of Deng's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics. The theory has proved to be a successful adoption
of Marxism perfectly fitted to the interim practice of reform in
modern China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Special Article: Great Banner (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The essence of the theory on emancipating the mind and seeking
truth from facts can be traced to Marxism-Leninism and Mao Zedong
Thought," according to Yang Chungui, vice-president of the Party
School of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's delivery of the report at the 14th CPC National
Congress continues to reverberate even today. Jiang called for
the Party to unswervingly persevere in improving and accelerating
the reform, opening-up and socialist modernization drives.
</P>
<P>
The Party's adherence to Deng's theory will ensure fulfilment
of the dream for a stable and prosperous China, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core has
adopted a series of major measures designed to promote the study,
research and publicity of the theory on building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
For example, the third volume of "Selections From Deng
Xiaoping" has been meticulously compiled and published, with the
first and second volumes revised and expanded prior to
publication. A series of symposia on the aforementioned third
volume have been held for principal leading officials at the
provincial and ministerial levels, in addition to three national
symposia covering the subject. A grand documentary on Deng
Xiaoping has been produced and released.
</P>
<P>
The high tide on studying Deng's theory, an activity which
enjoys the active involvement of the populace, is in full swing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Special Article: Great Banner (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A full understanding on the part of the general public will
accelerate the momentum of the great theory and promote the
country's material progress.
</P>
<P>
A number of achievements the Party Central Committee with Jiang
Zemin at the core has scored over the past five years as a result
of holding high the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory on building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
For example, since the 14th National Party Congress in 1992,
the Party Central Committee has endorsed the establishment of a
socialist market economy as the ultimate goal of the nation's
economic restructuring, and has carefully designed the basic
framework for the new market economic structure.
</P>
<P>
The central leadership of the CPC has also pointed out the
Party's critical role in solving China's current problems, and has
in turn introduced a series of measures to strengthen efforts to
build the Party.
</P>
<P>
The Party also presented a magnificent blueprint for China's
future development by drafting the Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000) for National Economic and Social Development and the
Long-Term Targets for the Year 2010, and has at the same time
strengthened efforts to promote the socialist ethical and
cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
The entire Party has the solemn duty to hold high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory on building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
It called for serious studies of Deng's theory, and
appropriately applying the theory in practice.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the country's reform, opening-up and
modernization drives have entered a critical period urgently
necessitates using Deng Xiaoping's theory on building socialism
with Chinese characteristics to study new situations and solve new
problems.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jinshan, deputy secretary of the Provincial Party
Committee in east China's Zhejiang Province and deputy to the 15th
national Party congress, is quoted as saying that anyone who
agrees to hold high the banner of Deng's theory must resolutely
safeguard the authority of the Party Central Committee with Jiang
at the core.
</P>
<P>
This represents the fundamental interests of the entire Party
and people from all ethnic groups across the country, and serves
as a critical guarantee for the Party's everlasting unity and
strength, as well as the country's long-term prosperity and
stability, Wang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
