<HEADLINE> China, Central Asian Countries Joining Hands for Trade Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 5 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 participants in
an on-going international symposium here are discussing various
issues concerning economic and trade cooperation between China and
five countries in central Asia.
</P>
<P>
The participants include delegations from Kazakhstan,
Uzbekistan, Kirghizstan, Turkmenistan, and Tadzhikistan, as well
as government officials and business people from cities alongside
the Euroasia Continental Bridge.
</P>
<P>
"China and central Asian countries can greatly complement each
other in economic structure. They should have the same policy
approach to intensify economic cooperation and trade exchanges,"
said Liu Xiangdong, assistant to the Chinese Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A United Nations official also promised to allocate special
funds to provide technological assistance for industrial
investment, border trade, poverty alleviation, and environmental
protection along the new Euroasia Continental Bridge.
</P>
<P>
The event is scheduled to end tomorrow. It is jointly sponsored
by the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
and the local government of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
</TEXT>
