<HEADLINE> S. Africa Condemns Suicide Jerusalem Explosions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has
condemned the suicide bomb explosions in central Jerusalem
Thursday which killed seven people and injured over 170 others.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued from Pretoria available here today, the
Foreign Ministry said such acts were perpetrated by extremist
forces whose main aim was to prevent the peace process in the
Middle East.
</P>
