<HEADLINE> 24 More Gold Medals Offered at Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Athletes at the 2000 Sydney
Olympics will compete for 295 gold medals, comparing with those of
271 in Atlanta, according to the Sydney Organising Committee for
the Olympic Games on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one of the 24 extra gold medals will be decided in
women's events of nine sports in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
If the international federations approve women's water polo,
women's pole vault and women's hammer throw, the number will
increase again.
</P>
<P>
Women athletes will be competing in 24 of the 28 sports at the
2000 Olympics, only missing out on baseball, boxing, modern
pentathlon and wrestling.
</P>
<P>
Triathlon and taekwondo, new sports introduced for the Sydney
Olympics, and the canoe/kayak slalom will provide equal
opportunity for women's participation. 
</P>
