<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Achieve Cotton Output Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is expected to
achieve its target of 10 million bales of cotton this year, each
weighing 170 kilograms despite recent floods and torrential rains,
the Pakistan Central Cotton Committee officials said.
</P>
<P>
Cotton sowing in central Punjab province and southern Sindh
province had exceeded the target of 2.9 million hectares,
registering a 3 percent increase over last year, the officials
said.
</P>
<P>
The recent flooding in Punjab had "minutely affected" the
cotton crop while the rains so far had a better impact on the
crop, they said.
</P>
<P>
Punjab is expected to produce 8.4 million bales of cotton while
Sindh is likely to harvest about 1.6 million bales, they said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan is one of the largest cotton producers in the world.
Exports of cotton and its products contributed more than 60
percent of the country's total exports of around 8.7 billion U.S.
dollars during the fiscal year from July 1995 to June 1996.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan produced 8.78 million bales of cotton last year
against the target of 10 million. The shortfall was blamed on pest
attack, lack of rain and use of substandard seeds by some key
cultivators.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
