<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Export of Leather Products Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's export of leather
and leather products has drastically declined during the month of
July due to high production costs and lack of proper adjustment
between the Pakistani rupees and a number of foreign currencies.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the Pakistan Tanners Association, in
July, leather export had declined by 21.52 percent while that of
leather products by 25.16 as compared to the corresponding month
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Major European currencies have adjusted downwards by 13 to 18
percent against the U.S. dollar during the last four months.
However, there has been no adjustment in the Pakistani rupee
during this period, which has resulted in high production costs
and decline in exports, the sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
