<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Restricts Use of Freon-Gas Refrigeration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will restrict the use
of freon-gas-run refrigerators and airconditioners for fish and
prawn cold storage, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted an announcement of the Ministry of Livestock
and Fisheries as saying that the authorities would not permit
installation of this kind of machines for storage of fishery
products in the future and would gradually replace them with
Ammonia-gas-run ones.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said that freon-gas refrigeration has not been
permitted in developed countries under the resolutions of the 1992
United Nations Copenhagen Convention which ban ozone-depleting
chemicals in developed countries after 1996 and allow use for 10
years in developing countries like Myanmar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Airline May Suffer Heavy Loss This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan International
Airlines Corporation (PIA) is likely to suffer heavy financial
loss in the 1997-98 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the airline anticipated that the financial loss of
the national flag carrier may rise to around 3.5 billion rupee
(about 87 million U.S. dollars) this year.
</P>
<P>
The present management, which had inherited around 6.25 billion
rupee (about 156 million dollars) of overdraft, had added up
another 2.25 billion rupee (about 56 million dollars) in the
ongoing financial crisis at the airline, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The total PIA earnings during the last financial year were
around 22.9 billion rupee (about 570 million dollars), the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned PIA which was graded as top ten among the world
airlines in the 1970s is now ranked 41st among about 240 carriers
of the world.
</P>
<P>
Plagued with financial problems, over-staffing and decreasing
quality of services, the airline profitability has registered a
decline in the past several years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
