<HEADLINE> Bangkok's Office Oversupply to Rise This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Despite oversupply, about
621,000 square meters of new office space is expected to come on
the market in Bangkok by the end of this year, according to a real
estate consultant.
</P>
<P>
Of the new supply, about 297,000 square meters, or 48 percent,
is located in the central business district, studies of real
estate consultant Jones Lang Wootton (Thailand) show.
</P>
<P>
However, demand for office space declined this year,
particularly from the cash-strapped financial sector which was hit
by a currency crisis recently. At the end of June, the average
vacancy rate in the central business district stood at 13.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Real estate oversupply has lasted for about four years, leaving
the banking and finance sectors being ridden with a huge amount of
non-performing loans or bad debt.  
</P>
