<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manufacturers, Sellers Required to Repurchase Styrofoam Food Containers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Manufacturers and marketers of
styrofoam food containers in the Chinese capital are required to
repurchase used products starting this month.
</P>
<P>
The production of styrofoam food containers will henceforth be
prohibited according to recent regulations jointly promulgated by
the Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau and Industrial and
Commercial Authorities.
</P>
<P>
The regulations are designed to eliminate so-called "white
pollution" created by 800,000 styrofoam containers
discarded throughout the city on a daily basis.
</P>
<P>
The regulations stipulate that, effective September 1 this
year, manufacturers and sellers should pay two yuan for each kg of
used styrofoam boxes recovered, with the rate of recovery targeted
at 30 percent for 1998, 50 percent for 1999, and 60 percent for
2000.
</P>
<P>
Nine recycling sites have been designated across the city. The
retrieved containers will be categorized, cleaned and processed
into other recycled plastic products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970905.0239 </DOCNO>
