<HEADLINE> Pakistan Downs Nepal 2-0 in Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATMANDU, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan beat Nepal 2-0 in
the opening game of the first South Asian Football Federation
Championship that began in Katmandu on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Paksitan led 1-0 after Muhammad Nauman opened the score in the
28th minutes when the Nepalese goalkeeper Upendra Man Singh rushed
ahead leaving the goal wide open.
</P>
<P>
In the 18th minute of the second half, Muhammad Ijaz struck to
put Pakistan two goals ahead.
</P>
<P>
Nepal will meet Sri Lanka in another group match on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka are in Group A of the
Championship while India, Bangladesh and the Maldives are in Group
B. 
</P>
