<HEADLINE> Argentina to Build Gigantic Fertilizer Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Argentina will build a
gigantic fertilizer-manufacturing plant capable of producing more
than one million tons of fertilizers a year.
</P>
<P>
This plant will give added value to Argentine Natural Gas,
since it's products will substitute for fertilizer imports for
more than 250 million U.S. dollars a year, a press release from
the company said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the plant will manufacture more than one million
tons a year of urea and 80,000 tons of ammonia, thus becoming the
biggest of its kind in the world.
</P>
<P>
The investment for this project is approximately 600 million
dollars and it is foreseen that the construction will start at the
end of this year. The plant will be put into operation in 2000,
according to the press release.
</P>
<P>
According to an official document on environmental approval and
zoning that authorizes the construction, the plant, to be
established in Ciudad de Bahia Blanca, province of Buenos Aires,
will be able to meet relevant international standards of
environment preservation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
