<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Beats Thailand in U-17 World Cup Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Host Egypt defeated Asia's
second-ranked team Thailand 3-2 in the opening match of the 7th
Under-17 world championship here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Egypt, ranked first in Africa, staged a number of strong
charges but tied with Thailand 1-1 in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian striker Ahmed Belal scored twice, in the 15th minute
of the first half and less than 60 seconds into the second half,
driving the 100,000 home fans in the Cairo Stadium into ecstasy.
</P>
<P>
Within 18 minutes, Arabi Mahmoud slipped a third ball into the
net, enabling his team to prevail over Thailand 3-1.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's Suksomkit Sutee made a beautiful quick revenge three
minutes later to pull the score to 2-3.
</P>
<P>
Thailand, the debutant at the championship, played a close game
with Egypt. It could have drawn the match if a blast in the last
30 seconds had not hit the post.
</P>
<P>
Chile and Germany will play here Friday in the second match of
Group A.
</P>
<P>
Group D goes into action on Friday, when defending champion
Ghana meets Argentina and Cost Rica tackles Bahrain in Port Said.
</P>
<P>
Sweeping aside Thailand, Egypt still faces other tough
competitions from Oman and Germany in the first round of the
tournament that runs through September 21.
</P>
<P>
Participating in this international event are 16 teams from
five continents. An unprecedented 80 teams had competed for one of
these 16 slots in the earlier qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
Egypt won the right to host the event last May, beating the
competitor New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
It is also the first time that this tournament takes place in
Africa since its inauguration in Beijing, China, in 1985.
</P>
<P>
FIFA President Joao Havelange said at the opening ceremony
Thursday that Africa is making an ever stronger performance in
football.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, he also predicted that given the Egyptian team's
strong performance in the qualifying stage, "It could secure, if
not first place, at least one of the top four slots."  
</P>
</TEXT>
