<HEADLINE> Jail Break Plans Foiled in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Prisoners including
Colombian drug traffickers in a jail here have planned an escape
during the coming inauguration of the Canal Universal Congress,
police said today.
</P>
<P>
The international congress to be held on September 7-10 would
serve as the distraction for a jailbreak, according to the plan
made by Colombian drug cartels and jail police officials.
</P>
<P>
Authorities discovered the plan after a patient investigation
that led to the capture of two lieutenants and a sub-lieutenant
suspected to be involved in the abortive flight.
</P>
<P>
The drug traffickers and the notorious criminal Jose Maria
Infanson paid the jail officers 200,000 U.S. dollars in cash for
facilitating their flee.
</P>
<P>
The criminals planned to escape the prison when the security
agencies concentrate themselves on the conference after the
arrival of high-ranking foreign dignitaries.
</P>
<P>
Besides providing the 200,000 dollars, Colombian drug cartels
had also rented vehicles and a speedboat for taking the escapees
to Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The police officers involved in the escape plan face sentences
of three to five years in prison. Endiem


nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
