<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Intl. Aid Program Reduces Infant Mortality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- An international aid program
is helping save the lives of women and children in central China's
Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the United Nations Children's Fund and Fund for
Population Activities have granted 650,000 US dollars and medical
equipment to update hospitals for women and children in 16
counties in the landlocked province of Hunan, one of the country's
major grain growing bases.
</P>
<P>
Medical care for women and children has reduced the mortality
of lying-in women, infants and children under age of five by one
third.
</P>
<P>
In 1986, 40 out of every 1,000 infants died at birth, with the
mortality rate for pregnant or lying-in women standing at
95 per 100,000.
</P>
<P>
The province's well-equipped health care net for women and
children is staffed by competent professionals. Some 80 percent of
clinics and hospitals at the township level feature maternity
wards and have the capacity to provide emergency care for pregnant
women and infants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
