<HEADLINE> China Publishes US Bestseller "Emotional Intelligence" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese version of US
bestseller titled "Emotional Intelligence" by Daniel Goleman has
emerged as a hit at its debut in a national book fair in
Changchun.
</P>
<P>
The work published in China is to introduce the revolutionary
concept of human intelligence to millions of Chinese readers,
according to officials with Shanghai Science and Technology
Publishing House, the Chinese publisher.
</P>
<P>
The book advocates that the intelligence quotient (IQ)
contributes only 20 percent to a person's success, with the
remaining 80 percent are determined by emotional intelligence
which can be enhanced through proper education.  
</P>
</TEXT>
