<HEADLINE> Jinan Launches Green Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Jinan, capital of east China's
Shandong Province, is launching a green project to turn the city
into a "large park," said an official of the Jinan Bureau of Parks and
Woods.
</P>
<P>
Jinan is to build 600,000 square meters of lawn, remove walls
around scenic areas and plant trees and grass along 18 main
streets to form green corridors within three years, the official
noted.
</P>
<P>
The whole project is expected to cost 15 million yuan
1.8 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The city plans to increase its green area overage to about 31
percent by the end of this year, with 5.2 square meters per person.
</P>
<P>
Green land protection regulations will soon be issued in
Jinan, the official added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
