<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Nino To Cause Peru Losses of $1.2 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The El Nino climate phenomenon
will cause losses amounting to 1.2 billion U.S. dollars to Peru
this year, said Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori.
</P>
<P>
During a tour of north Peru to inspect preventive works,
Fujimori said Wednesday that El Nino has caused fishing losses of
300 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The president said that disasters brought by El Nino will
reduce the country's gross domestic product (GDP) by 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the 7.2 percent growth rate foreseen for this year
will drop to 5 percent because of the phenomenon, he said.
</P>
<P>
The president deplored that the population does not have enough
knowledge about the El Nino effects.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that rains caused by El Nino will destroy some
800 houses in the department of Tumbes, but 1,000 temporary houses
will be built. 
</P>
</TEXT>
