<HEADLINE> Central China City Uses Resources to Attract Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, Semptember 5 (Xinhua) -- The hills and water of
Chenzhou city in central China's Hunan province are expected to
help it become better known to the outsiders.
</P>
<P>
A "Mountain-and-Water Tourism Festival" will be held later this
month in the city for the first time to introduce its tourism resources
to the world.
</P>
<P>
Chenzhou's hisatory goes back more than 2,000 years. Its
name means a "city surrounded by forests". Its forest coverage is
57.5 percent, about four times the country's average.
</P>
<P>
According to Mei Kebao, Secretary of the Chenzhou City
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, the city has the only
hunting park open to foreigners in south China, and "Tourists can
enjoy mountain streams, labyrinth-like caves, forestry parks, and
hot springs here," he explained.
</P>
<P>
Chenzhou is the "south gate" of Hunan province and is near
other famous tourist places like Hengshan Mount and Jinggangshan
Mount. It is about nine hours by train from Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
