<HEADLINE> Chinese Express Confidence in National Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The vast majority of Chinese
citizens have full confidence in the national economy, as well as
prospects for increased income and employment opportunities.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey revealed a consumer confidence index level of
73.6 percent, up 3.9 percentage points on the end of last year and
fourth among on the list of 13 countries and regions surveyed
during the biannual MasterCard International survey of the
Asia-Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
The recent survey indicated that residents in three major
Chinese cities -- Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou -- are
optimistic about their quality of life, overall national economic
performance and individual income anticipated for the foreseeable
future.
</P>
<P>
China's comprehensive confidence index from a sixth place
ranking in 1996 to fourth place behind Indonesia, Malaysia and
the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The survey results also suggested that Hong Kong residents have
high hope for the local economy, with the consumer confidence index
reaching 76 percent, up 10.1 percentage points on the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
MasterCard International has conducted the survey in the
Asian-Pacific Region since 1993 in order to determine consumer
confidence in the economic prospects for their respective
countries. MasterCard provides the information and data gathered
from the survey to over 23,000 member banks and financial
companies across the globe.  
</P>
</TEXT>
