<HEADLINE> China Takes Men's Team Title at World Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China carried on their
all-around domination to win the title of the men's team event at
the 1997 World Gymnastics Championships here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team of Huang Xu, Li Xiaopeng, Lu Yufu, Shen Jian,
Xiao Junfeng, and Zhang Jinjing, kept their lead to clinch a total
winning points of 226.11 through each of the six events of vault,
bars, horizonal bar, floor, pommel horse, and rings.
</P>
<P>
Before Huang Xu finished his competition on the rings, the
Chinese gymnasts had already got 224.617 points, assuring
themselves the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Belarus, the fourth in the qualifying round, got the second
place with 221.568 and Russia, the second in the qualifying round,
finished in third with 220.682.
</P>
<P>
In the fourth to sixth places were Japan (220.643), United
States (219.806), and Germany (217.834). 
</P>
