<HEADLINE> Tianjin Records Increasing Number of Cornea Donators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 5 (Xinhua)-- The new eye bank in Tianjin, a
port city in north China, has attracted a growing number of
supporters.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,000 Tianjin residents have visited the Tianjin
Ophthalmological Hospital following the public announcement of its
opening to express their willingness to donate their corneas upon
death.
</P>
<P>
Local health officials note that the youngest donor to make the
commitment was only 12 years old.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is home to over 40,000 blind people who need cornea
transplants to regain their eyesight. However, only 20 to 30
transplants can be performed each year due to a shortage of
corneas.
</P>
<P>
The warm response from eye donors has raised hope for more
blind people, according to health officials. 
</P>
