<HEADLINE> Sino-US Elevator Maker Grabs Quarter of Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin Otis Elevator Co.,
Ltd, a joint venture formed by US Otis Elevator Co. and local
partners in Tianjin, a port city in north China, has taken a
quarter of the Chinese market after 13 years of operation.
</P>
<P>
Recognized as one of the fastest growing Otis subsidiaries
worldwide, the venture has registered an annual net sales increase
of around 400 to 500 million yuan in successive years, according
to Huang Xiong, president of Tianjin Otis.
</P>
<P>
After two capital fundings in the past two years, the joint
venture's investment now totals 78 million US dollars while the
assets hit nearly 200 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, the company has run five factories that follow
the latest elevator-manufacturing technology.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise has mapped out a plan to turn the company into
Otis's production base in Asia in the next five years, Huang said.
</P>
<P>
Otis, the world leader in elevator manufacturing, also has
joint ventures in other Chinese cities, including Beijing,
Guangzhou and Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
