<HEADLINE> Rafter Advances to Semifinals at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Australian Patrick Rafter
advanced to the semifinals of the U.S. Open tennis championships
Thursday by beating Magnus Larsson of Sweden in straight sets at
the National Tennis Center in New York.
</P>
<P>
The 13th seed Rafter achieved the victory by overpowering the
Swede with 7-6 6-4 6-2 in the quarter-finals on a sunny, cool day.
</P>
<P>
The Australian won four of the last five points to capture the
first set tiebreaker 7-4, and then used a service break in the
seventh game of the second set to take a 4-3 advantage before
serving out for a two-set lead.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, a runner-up in five tournaments this year, broke
Larsson in the fifth and seventh games of the final set to
complete the match.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's semifinals, the 24-year-old Rafter will meet the
winner of Thursday night quarter-final between second-seeded
American Michael Chang and 10th seed Marcelo Rios of Chile.
</P>
<P>
The other men's semifinal will be held between Canadian-born
Briton Greg Rusedski and Sweden's Jonas Bjorkman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
