<HEADLINE> Bollegraf, Leach Claim First Title at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Fifth-seeded duo Manon
Bollegraf of the Netherlands and American Rick Leach claimed the
the mixed doubles crown, the first title of this year's U.S. Open
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
They defeated the Argentine combination of Mercedes Paz and
Pablo Albano in the mixed doubles final.
</P>
<P>
Bollegraf and Leach, who also teamed up to win the Australian
Open title this year, won the third-set tiebreak 7-3 to claim a
3-6 7-5 7-6 victory in one hour and 49 minutes at Flushing, New
York.
</P>
<P>
The winners shared a top prize of 100,000 U.S. dollars and the
Argentines split 50,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
They made the most of their opportunities by cashing in on each
of their three break points in the match. But Paz and Albano were
successful on only three of 10 break points they reached.
</P>
<P>
Leach said after the match that he had got the positive
influence from the 23-year-old Bollegraf, who also partnered
Nicole Arendt to reach the women's doubles final at Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Leach, who had four Grand Slam men's doubles
titles and three mixed titles before the Open final, said, "We
stayed together and got some lucky breaks at the end." 
</P>
</TEXT>
