<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yellow River Diversion Tunnels Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Three water diversion
tunnels for the Xiaolangdi water control project in the middle
reaches of the Yellow River have been fully completed.
</P>
<P>
The diversion tunnels, with an average length of 1,100 m and a
sectional diameter of 14.5 m, are key facilities for the
Xiaolangdi project which is funded by the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Xiaolangdi project, located 40 km north of Luoyang City in
central China's Henan Province, is the largest multipurpose
dam project on the Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the project commenced in 1994 and is scheduled
for completion within 11 years. Fourteen companies from Germany,
Italy, France and China are engaged in the construction effort.
</P>
<P>
The project will need an estimated 36.47 billion yuan (4.39
billion U.S. dollars), which includes 1.2 billion US dollars in
loans from the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the river to be dammed in October this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
