<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Weakness of blue-chip issues
weighed down the Dow industrials, but broader stock measures rose
today and smaller-company shares pushed further into record
territory.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 27.40 to 7,867.24 after
recovering over the final hour from a 76-point drop.
</P>
<P>
All other popular stock measures posted modest gains, however,
with the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies cruising to its
sixth consecutive record high and its ninth straight winning
session.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a nearly 8-to-7
margin on the NYSE, where volume was heavy again at 559.33 million
shares, up slightly from Wednesday's 548.72 million.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 3.01 to 930.87, the
NYSE composite index rose 1.40 to 485.11, and the Nasdaq composite
index rose 6.39 to 1,624.63.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 0.92 to 429.71, and the American Stock
Exchange composite, which has a large constituency of smaller
companies, closed at a record high for the third straight day,
rising 2.26 to 662.26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
