<HEADLINE> S. Africa Tests Weapons for Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's
state-owned arms producer DENEL recently did successful weapon
testing for a Swedish manufacturer at its Overberg missile test
range in Western Cape Province, local television reported today.
</P>
<P>
The test range near Arniston, until recently highly secret,
is becoming more accessible as DENEL sought paying customers
from overseas, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The range was built at a cost of hundreds of millions of
Rands.
</P>
<P>
DENEL's General Manager Jan Malan said that the range is
important to South Africa's arms industry because it allows "the
clever buying and use of equipment", and the demonstration to
buyers of the company's equipment. 
</P>
