<HEADLINE> Canadian Minister to Promote Trade With Brazil Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Canadian International Trade
Minister Sergio Marchi will visit Brazil next week in a bid to
enhance trade and investment ties and to underscore Canada's
strong support for hemispheric free trade.
</P>
<P>
"It is vitally important to maintain momentum towards a Free
Trade Area of the Americas in preparation for next spring's
Santiago Summit," Marchi said today.
</P>
<P>
During his four-day trip to Brazil, Marchi will attend a World
Economic Forum summit of regional political leaders focusing on
hemispheric integration.
</P>
<P>
At the summit, he will meet with his counterparts from several
countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to discuss issues such as progress on work
toward a Free Trade Area of the Americas, the status of talks
aimed at developing closer links with South America's largest
trade grouping Mercosur, and ways to increase Canada-Mercosur
trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
Marchi will also attend a round-table discussion with members
of the Canada-Brazil Chamber of Commerce in Belo Horizonte.
</P>
<P>
In addition to business activities, Marchi will unveil a plaque
commemorating the 50th anniversary of the Canadian Consulate
General in San Paulo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
