<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, Waiting US Jobs Data </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
ended mixed in thin trading volumes today, with many dealers
remaining cautious ahead of Friday's US monthly payrolls figures.
</P>
<P>
British shares in London made modest gains, with the FTSE 100
index up 14.4 points or 0.29 percent at 4,991.3 by close, as
stronger futures helped to offset a weak performance on Wall
Street.
</P>
<P>
A Confederation of British Industry survey showing a slowdown
in retail sales growth also helped sentiment by easing interest
rate rise fears.
</P>
<P>
However, the DAX-30 index in Frankfurt ended lower, with many
investors on the sidelines ahead of US payroll figures Friday. The
index fell 31.97 points to 4,071.68 by the end of the session.
</P>
<P>
French stocks recovered from an early slide as bonds came off
lows although trading was cautious ahead of US economic data. The
CAC-40 index finished up 9.07 points at 2,926.99. 
</P>
