<HEADLINE> Cameroonian Officials Urged to Promote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of
Cameroun's Ministry of Agriculture were urged today to use their
technical knowledges to promote agricultural production and help
pull the country out of economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Agustin Kodock, Minister of State in charge of agriculture,
made the remarks here this morning while opening the annual
conference of the ministry of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Kodock called on senior officials in his ministry to adopt a
new approach toward their relations with the farmers in the rural
areas.
</P>
<P>
Much have been done during the past three years to organized
farmers in the rural areas into cooperative groups or farmers'
associations and to get funds from international organizations to
finance small agricultural projects in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 participants attending the conference will
discuss on the functioning of agricultural services, the running
of projects, the management of budgetary allocations and reforms
of agricultural training.
</P>
<P>
The conference will end tomorrow with recommendations on how
to improve agricultural activities in the country in the era of
economic globalization. 
